'''Smarthinking''' is an academic [[online tutoring]] service, provided by [[Pearson Education]]. The service provides on-demand support from tutors in over 25 subjects. Smarthinking uses a [[Pedagogy|pedagogical]] approach along with whiteboard interface technology to connect students and tutors.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.pearsoned.com/news/pearson-announces-smarthinking-online-tutoring-service-enhancements-to-improve-institutional-and-learner-outcomes/#.VGuyuPldWSq |title=Pearson Announces Smarthinking Online Tutoring Service Enhancements to Improve Institutional and Learner Outcomes &#124; Pearson News |website=Pearsoned.com |date=2014-11-10 |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>

Smarthinking launched in 1999 to provide real-time assistance for students in postsecondary education.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pearsoned.com/higher-education/products-and-services/smarthinking/about-us/ |title=About Us &#124; Smarthinking &#124; Pearson |website=Pearsoned.com |date= |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> In 2007, Smarthinking was honored with the Software & Information Industry Association (SIIA) CODie award for Best Instruction Solutions for Students at Home.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.brighthub.com/education/online-learning/reviews/25812.aspx |title=Need an Online Tutoring Program and Writing Service? Think About Smarthinking! |website=Brighthub.com |date=2011-06-29 |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>

==History==
In an effort to expand its offerings, Pearson Education acquired Smarthinking in February 2011. December 1, 2011 Smarthinking launched its new discipline of support for reading.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pr.com/press-release/373682 |title=Smarthinking Launches Reading Tutoring Support Services |website=PR.com |date=2011-12-03 |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> Tutors could perform live sessions in core areas of vocabulary,  reading and comprehension. In 2012, Pearson reported the addition of Liberal Arts Math to its Math services.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.pearsoned.com/news/smarthinking-launches-liberal-arts-math-online-tutoring-support-services/ |title=Smarthinking Launches Liberal Arts Math Online Tutoring Support Services &#124; Pearson News |website=Pearsoned.com |date=2012-02-22 |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref> To date Smarthinking has over 1500 tutors, and has completed between  6 and 7 million tutoring sessions. It's headquartered in 1919 M. St., NW Suite 600 Washington, DC 20036.

==Leadership==
Smarthinking leadership team is composed of former college professors and experts in their disciplines.

Christa Ehmann Powers, Ph.D. has served as Vice President & Chief Education Officer since Smarthinking’s launch in 1999, and heads the development of online tutoring and instructional services in the United States and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pearsoned.com/higher-education/products-and-services/smarthinking/about-us/ |title=About Us &#124; Smarthinking &#124; Pearson |website=Pearsoned.com |date= |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>

==Results==
Pearson- conducted efficacy studies on the effectiveness of Smarthinking have shown the impact of usage, including:

• Students using Smarthinking at Volunteer State Community College were eight times more likely to successfully complete their courses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pearsonmylabandmastering.com/northamerica/results/files/CCR_WEB_FINAL.pdf#page=34 |title=Smarthinking : Case study |website=Pearsonmylabandmastering.com |date= |accessdate=2016-07-30}}</ref>

